{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀπειλέω</b>, <br /> <br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1><i>3rd.pers.</i><i>dual</i> <i>imperfect</i> <i>active</i> ἀπειλήτην, <i>Epic dialect</i> for ἠπειλείτην, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.313\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: later <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>present</i> ἀπειλείω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Musaeus Epicus 122, 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 20.204\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]:— <b>hold out</b> either in the way of <b>promise</b> or <b>threat,</b> and therefore: <br /><Level2><b>__B.I</b></Level2> sometimes in good sense, <b>promise,</b> οὐδ᾽ ἠπείλησεν ἄνακτι.. ῥέξειν κλειτὴν ἑκατόμβην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.863, compare 872\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>boast</b> or <b>brag,</b> ὥς ποτ᾽ ἀπειλήσει.1; ἦ μὲν ἀπείλησας βητάρμονας εἶναι ἀρίστους[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.383, compare 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 2.57a. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.II</b></Level2> commonly in bad sense, <b>threaten,</b> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus either _absolutely_, as 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.665, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.368: or (more frequently) with _dative_ _person_, [prev. work] 20.272, etc.: c._accusative_ _cognate_, αἶψα δ᾽ ἀναστὰς ἠπείλησεν μῦθον\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>spake a threatening</b> speech, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.388\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπειλὰς ἀ., see at {ἀπειλ; δείν᾽ ἀπειλήσων ἔπη} [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 542\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: frequently with <i>neuter</i> <i>pronoun</i> or <i>adjective</i>, ἀ. τόγε θυμῷ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.212\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ταῦτα, πολλὰ ἀ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.18, 1.111, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.33, etc.; πύργοις ἀ. δεινά 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 426; τοῦτ᾽ ἀπειλήσας ἔχεις 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 817. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> of the thing threatened, θάνατον ἀ. ὃς ἂν..[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.81; ξίφος 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pompeius” 47; ζημίας ἀ. κατά τινος [prev. author] “Cam.” 39\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἠπείλησαν τοὺς ἄρχοντας <b>threatened</b> <b>them with</b> the prefects, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Orationes” 47.7. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.3</b></Level3> dependent clauses were added in <i>future</i> <i>infinitive</i>, γέρας.. ἀφαιρήσεσθαι ἀπειλεῖς[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.161, compare 15.179, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.313; σφέας.. ἀπείλεε ἐκτρίψειν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.37; ἀ. δράσειν τι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 287; ἀ. ἀποκτενεῖν 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 3.28\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: rarely in <i>present</i> <i>infinitive</i>, ἠπ... ἑλκέμεν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.682: after 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] in <i>aorist</i> <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.5.4, “HG” 5.4.7, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 24.16. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.4</b></Level3> ἀ. ὅτι.., ὡς.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 88, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.5.22, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. τινί, εἰ μή.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cyr.” 4.5.12. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.III</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, ἀπειλοῦμαι, of persons, <b>to be terrified by threats,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Smp.” 4.31. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.III.2</b></Level3> of things, τὰ ἀπειληθέντα, ={ἀπειλαί}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 823c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.IV</b></Level2> later in <i>middle</i>, with <i>aorist 1</i> <b>-ησάμην</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Bella Civilia” 3.29, 2nd c.AD: Polyaenus Historicus 7.35.2\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>forbid with threats,</b> ἀπειλησώμεθα αὐτοῖς μηκέτι λαλεῖν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Act.4.17.\">NT</a>]","strongNumber":"G0546","accentedUnicode":"ἀπειλέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0547","matchingForm":"ἀπειλή","stepTransliteration":"apeilē","gloss":"threat","_zh_tw_Gloss":"威嚇","_es_Gloss":"amenaza","_zh_Gloss":"威吓"}],"shortDef":"to threaten, warn","mediumDef":"to threaten, warn <br /><b>to threaten, menace, warn, rebuke,</b> <ref='Act.4.17'>Acts 4:17;</ref> <ref='1Pe.2.23'>1Pet. 2:23</ref>*","stepGloss":"to threaten","stepTransliteration":"apeileō","count":2,"_es_Definition":"amenazar ; advertir","_zh_tw_Definition":"威脅, 警告 (徒 4:17; 彼前 2:23)","_zh_Definition":"威胁, 警告 (徒 4:17; 彼前 2:23)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"hăm dọa ; ngăm dọa","_zh_tw_Gloss":"威脅恐嚇","_es_Gloss":"amenazar","_zh_Gloss":"威胁恐吓"}]}